Shaggy0291 wrote:
fuzzeenavel wrote:it’s amazing that Japan is one of the richest, most technologically advanced countries on earth, with 1960s era social policies

It's not as surprising if you view the sensibilities of Japanese society through a historical lens. They went from a bonafide feudal society to a modern industrial one in the space of a generation during the Meiji era, with much of the social conventions of the time preserved. That entire process was piecemeal in Europe, with the stripping away of medieval baggage every step of the way.
